com.google.api.gax.grpc

Interface ChannelProvider


  • public interface ChannelProvider
    Provides an interface to hold and build the channel that will be used. If the channel does not already exist, it will be constructed when getOrBuildChannel(java.util.concurrent.Executor) is called. Implementations of ChannelProvider may choose to create a new ManagedChannel for each call to getOrBuildChannel(java.util.concurrent.Executor), or may return a fixed ManagedChannel instance. In cases where the same ManagedChannel instance is returned, for example by a ChannelProvider created using the ServiceApiSettings provideChannelWith(ManagedChannel, boolean) method, and shouldAutoClose returns true, the getOrBuildChannel(java.util.concurrent.Executor) method will throw an IllegalStateException if it is called more than once. This is to prevent the same ManagedChannel being closed prematurely when it is used by multiple client objects.

ConnectionSettings connectionSettings()

      • getOrBuildChannel

        io.grpc.ManagedChannel getOrBuildChannel(Executor executor)
                                  throws IOException
        Get the channel to be used to connect to the service. The first time this is called, if the channel does not already exist, it will be created. The Executor will only be used when the channel is created. For implementations returning a fixed ManagedChannel object, the executor is unused. If the ChannelProvider is configured to return a fixed ManagedChannel object and to return shouldAutoClose as true, then after the first call to getOrBuildChannel(java.util.concurrent.Executor), subsequent calls should throw an IllegalStateException. See interface level docs for ChannelProvider for more details.
        Throws:
        IOException
